  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Clinical Cure in the Clinically Evaluable (CE) Population at Test of Cure (TOC)</measure>
    <time_frame>Study days 14-38</time_frame>
    <description>Patients were considered cured if all systemic signs and symptoms of CAP present at screening were improved or resolved and no further antibiotic therapy was necessary. In addition, the follow-up chest X-ray was to be either stable or improved.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <other_outcome>
    <measure>Per Patient Microbiological Response of Eradicated in the Microbiologically Evaluable (ME) Population at Test of Cure (TOC)</measure>
    <time_frame>Study Days 14-38</time_frame>
